1.text: Pick a video call platform you both use.

2.text: Charge your device so it won’t die during the date.

3.text: Schedule your date in advance so it feels like an event.

4.text: Tell your date if you're uncomfortable with them recording the call.

5.text: Send flirty messages to build anticipation if you're in a relationship.

6.text: Dress up like you’re going out, especially if it's a new relationship.

7.text: Choose a well-lit area to stage your video call.

8.text: Arrange the area where you’re filming so it looks nice.

9.text: Position your camera at a flattering angle.

10.text: Do a practice call or test video before a first date.

11.text: Look into the camera when you talk instead of watching the video.

12.text: Be yourself instead of trying to be perfect.

13.text: Try to limit your fidgeting if you've just started dating.

14.text: Keep your comments positive if you're still getting to know each other.

15.text: Prepare questions for a first date in case there's an awkward silence.

16.text: Have a drink together for an easy first date.

17.text: Share a meal together if you want a conventional date.

18.text: Do a round of 20 questions to get to know each other better.

19.text: Watch and discuss a movie if you're in the mood for a film.

20.text: Recreate a sip-n-paint date if you like being creative.

21.text: Try stargazing if you want a romantic, late-night date.

22.text: Go on a digital tour of a museum or city for a cultural experience.

23.text: Play an online or board game for a fun, interactive date.
